Sec. 61.015. SEIZURE OF SEED NOT IN COMPLIANCE. (a) The
department may sue in a court of competent jurisdiction in the area
in which the seed is located for the seizure of any lot of
agricultural or vegetable seed that is not in compliance with this
chapter.
(b) If the court finds that the seed is not in compliance with
this chapter, the court may condemn the seed. Condemned seed shall
be denatured, processed, destroyed, relabeled, or otherwise disposed
of in accordance with the law of this state.
(c) The court may not condemn the seed unless the owner or
custodian of the seed is given the opportunity to apply to the court
for the release of the seed or for permission to condition or relabel
the seed to bring it into compliance with this chapter.
Acts 1981, 67th Leg., p. 1131, ch. 388, Sec. 1, eff. Sept. 1, 1981.

